  "response": "While AI and machine translation have improved significantly, they are unlikely to completely replace human interpreters and translators in the next 10 years. Current AI translation has limitations:\n\n1. Complex nuance and context understanding\n2. Cultural subtleties and idiomatic expressions\n3. High-stakes or sensitive communication scenarios\n4. Technical or specialized language domains\n\nHuman translators will likely continue working alongside AI tools, using them as productivity aids rather than being fully replaced. The most probable scenario is a collaborative human-AI approach.",
